title: The Aesthetic theories of French Artists (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Aesthetic Theories of French Artists: From Realism to Surrealism
The Johns Hopkins Press | 1966 | ISBN: 0801802164 | English | 132 pages | PDF | 16 MB


This study is a modest attempt to trace some of the connections between art and other branches of human endeavor and culture in the history of ideas. Its thesis is that one should examine the history of ideas as it is manifested in art
